Creating images with R

My meme

The meme below shows how my lovely boy and girl grown from kittens to cats. The kitten picture was taken on 15/01/2022 when they are still very young and small. The cats picture was taken on 13/05/2022 and theyve grown up a lot but still accompany each other. Its really a lovely vibe, and I am so glad that I recorded these heart-warming moment!

For more pictures of my loves, click here to view

# input and use the magick package install if it's not in your computer
library(magick)

# read the kittens and cats image and using pipe operator
kittens <- image_read("https://i.imgur.com/KYJ5ZUG.jpeg") %>%   
  image_resize("180x240!") %>%    # change the size
  image_convert("png")            # convert the image format to png

cats <- image_read("https://i.imgur.com/E7R1Py9.jpeg") %>%      
  image_resize("180x240!") %>%    # change the size
  image_convert("png")            # convert the image format to png

# create two blank image and customs
image_1 <- image_blank(width = 180, 
            height = 240,                           # choose size
            color = "#000000") %>%                  # pick a color
  image_annotate(text = "When we were\n kittens",   # add text
                 color = "#FFFFFF",                 # pick text color
                 size = 25,                         # choose text size
                 font = "Impact",                   # pick text font
                 gravity = "east")                  # choose text position

image_2 <- image_blank(width = 180, 
                       height = 240,                # choose size
                       color = "#FFFFFF") %>%       #.pick a color
  image_annotate(text = "When we\ngrow up",         # add text
                 color = "#000000",                 # pick text color
                 size = 25,                         # choose text size
                 font = "Impact",                   # pick text font
                 gravity = "west")                  # choose text position

# combine the pictures
part_1 <- image_append(c(image_1, kittens))         # combine the top half part

part_2 <- image_append(c(cats, image_2))            # combine the bottom half

cat_vector <- c(part_1, part_2)                     # combine 2 parts vertically
final_meme <- image_append(cat_vector, stack = TRUE)

image_write(final_meme, "my_meme.png")              # save and name your meme

My animated GIF

In this animated gif, the images in my meme are used to create the frames. The animation can viewers feel their growth visually easier. In addition, a funny question text is added into this gif, can you find the answer?

# copy the code from meme.R to get the images which are used in this animation
# here is the R-script from meme.R
# input and use the magick package install if it's not in your computer
library(magick)

# read the kittens and cats image and using pipe operator
kittens <- image_read("https://i.imgur.com/KYJ5ZUG.jpeg") %>%   
  image_resize("180x240!") %>%    # change the size
  image_convert("png")            # convert the image format to png

cats <- image_read("https://i.imgur.com/E7R1Py9.jpeg") %>%      
  image_resize("180x240!") %>%    # change the size
  image_convert("png")            # convert the image format to png

# create two blank image and customs
image_1 <- image_blank(width = 180, 
                       height = 240,                           # choose size
                       color = "#000000") %>%                  # pick a color
  image_annotate(text = "When we were\n kittens",   # add text
                 color = "#FFFFFF",                 # pick text color
                 size = 25,                         # choose text size
                 font = "Impact",                   # pick text font
                 gravity = "east")                  # choose text position

image_2 <- image_blank(width = 180, 
                       height = 240,                # choose size
                       color = "#FFFFFF") %>%       #.pick a color
  image_annotate(text = "When we\ngrow up",         # add text
                 color = "#000000",                 # pick text color
                 size = 25,                         # choose text size
                 font = "Impact",                   # pick text font
                 gravity = "west")                  # choose text position

# here is the new code for create an animation gif
# create frames by combining all image frame in meme.R
frames <- c(image_1, kittens, image_2, cats) 
animation_gif<- image_animate(frames, fps = 1) %>%
  image_annotate(text = "who is the girl?", size = 20, gravity = "south")

# save and name this gif
image_write(animation_gif, "my_animation.gif")
